reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Durable abd a lot of fun!
reviews.reviewText: These planes were easy to put together and the grandkids are enjoying them. The are very sturdy, fly far and just plain (haha) cool! They were bought for 2 girls 7 and 8, 2 rowdy boys 6 and 7!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Been a fun toy for the kids
reviews.reviewText: Does loops, or flys straight. Kids love it! Pretty durable too, just don't throw it in the camp fire.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Purchased these planes to keep a group of kids busy over Thanksgiving and boy did they deliver! They are fairly sturdy (had all ages handling them) and provided hours and hours of entertained. They were loved by all ages (3-10). The adults got in on the fun and played with them as well. I would purchase these again in a heartbeat. Great price and great entertainment!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cool planes, one broke while assembling.
reviews.reviewText: Got these today to replace a similar plane that was much larger. These planes are about 7 or 8 inches long and launch easily from the launcher. My 5 year old really likes it and likes the fact that he can do it himself. One of the planes broke in half while we were putting in the wings, but we were able to fix it with tape. We will see how long they last, but our first play with them it was a hit!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Oh kids love these planes
reviews.reviewText: They’re pretty durable they last throughout the year or two, and then we usually purchase more

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just buy them
reviews.reviewText: So much fun! We have the jet model of these, also. They take a bit for a young kid to figure out the body mechanics that ends in successful flight but once that happens....oh my, they soar! Fun for the kids to change the tail (I'm told it's called a horizontal stabilizer, who knew) to alter the flight. The lights are an added plus, however, if the kids are young and you live in a daylight savings zone....that feature is never fully experienced. Two, not surprising experiences with these; eventually, some of them ended up with the hard plastic (cockpit area) being broken; likely less of an issue when being used by a kid who's more proficient at throwing. Also, important to remind little kids to handle the movable parts with care and proper grasp, otherwise those styrofoam pieces break. For the price and the hours (literally) of fun, in the end, that part is really a non-issue.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars great way to keep little ones busy for a while
reviews.reviewText: great toy to occupy kids (maybe 10 and under) in wide open field type space. They fly good and do enough flips it keeps kids interested. Just avoid doing around your house...........unless you want to keep having to get them off roof.
